e Camp Policy Survey</span><hr size=1> Lagenduil,<br>
<br>
Your logic is extremely flawed.  The same rationale could be used for any named mob in EQ.  By your logic if you come down to Frenzy in Lower Guk and someone is there, you can just walk right up and whack him if he spawns.  The only difference is amount of time between spawns or place holder spawns.  You are correct, we on Sayrn made Ragefire a camp.  The sheer number of clerics who had reached the verant designated bottle neck became so great that people became willing to camp it for up to 72 hours instead of doing hit or miss for 6 months.  Another contributing factor to the matter is the great usefulness a guild gets out of having cleric epics.  It would be better if a &quot;waiting list&quot; could be made, as other servers have adopted.  We know of course that this will not work on Sayrn, we have far to many mercenary like guilds.<br>
<br>
E/Ragus  Guardians of Light <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulagenduil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lagenduil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#DDA0DD>(7/21/01 2:30:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Camp Policy Survey</span><hr size=1> The difference between a camp that requires killing placeholders and camping a spawn that doesn't have any is enormous. Killing the frenzy spawn you need the force there to keep it clear while waiting for it to spawn, killing phers and keeping the force there to at least attempt it when it spawns. Ragefire on the other hand has no placeholders, requires no force to camp except half a group to kill fire giants every 8 hours, and people sit there and lay claim to something they did nothing to deserve except stay idle.<br>
<br>
Comparing a multi-day camp, which only requires a person to hold according to people who &quot;respect the camp&quot;, to a 30 min semi-rare spawn, which requires upkeep, is pretty stupid. Also saying my logic if flawed because you can't apply what I said to every spawn in the game is also very stupid.<br>
<br>
My logic is not flawed, your understanding of the difference between the two is.<br>
<br>
As far as their willingness to camp Ragefire for 72 hours...thats great, camp it and get the people there when it pops, but don't EXPECT people to think that you DESERVE that spawn by sitting there for 72 hours. Just because you're willing to sit there for that long, doesn't mean you have to force other clerics wanting that piece to sit for the same length of time when thats not how it was intended.<br>
<br>
If you sit there for that long, ragefire pops and someone else comes in and takes it...well that really bites, but remember that by camping it you never had a real claim other than what others think. The unwritten rule was made by some players and unfortunately followed by most. That camp punishes every cleric looking to get their epic, it should not exist. Keeping the claim to ragefire via camping it around just makes it worse, the only thing you should gain by camping it is the knowledge its up. <br>
<br>
If you want to keep claim to it, have a force with you while you're camping it, so when it does pop you have the force to take it down. Its too hard to keep a force there you say? Well heres some info to you, epics weren't meant to be easy. Some were created very easy, others made easier because of their toughness, but they weren't intended to be easy...so don't think just by being a cleric you deserve yours.<br>
<br>
Why do I really care this much...I'm not a cleric. Oh yea its because players keep making such a big fuss over the whole thing. Wheres Garb with that dead horse trophy? <p><b>Robinn Ublinde 60 Assassin<br>
